The "Printers" window of the Windows 3.1 Control Panel is open and active.  At the top, a field displays "No Default Printer" indicating no default printer is currently set. Below, an empty list box labeled "Installed Printers:" suggests there are no printers currently installed. 

A scrollable list titled "List of Printers: Install Unlisted or Updated Printer" displays a variety of printer models. The mouse cursor hovers over this list, having just clicked the down arrow to reveal more options.  

Several buttons are enabled within the window:
- **"Set As Default Printer"** (greyed out): This button, currently inactive, is used to set the selected printer as the default.
- **"Connect..."**: This button likely manages network connections for a selected printer.
- **"Setup..."**: This button likely allows adjustments to the configuration of a selected printer.
- **"Remove"**: This button likely uninstalls a selected printer from the system.
- **"Add >>"**: This button likely adds a new printer to the "Installed Printers" list. 
- **"Install..."**: This button likely initiates the installation process for the printer selected in the "List of Printers."

A checkbox labeled **"Use Print Manager"** sits below the "Set As Default Printer" button. This option is unchecked, signifying that Print Manager, a utility for managing print jobs, is currently disabled.
